text:
7 West 96th Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Central Park West. This is the home of Mrs. Augusta E. Stetson, which connects with the First Church of Christ Scientist. Mrs. Stetson was the founder of this church, with direct permission both of Mother
Church in Boston and Mary Baker Eddy.
May 27, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
